Cricket South Africa JOHANNESBURG - Cricket SA's company secretary Welsh Gwaza has been suspended with full pay pending a disciplinary hearing.
Gwaza will be the first administrator to face disciplinary action after being implicated in the Fundudzi forensic report. READ: South African cricketers in 'despair' at administrative chaos He was given notice by CSA's interim board to appear in front of a DC committee on 14 December. Gwaza faces various allegations of misconduct. He has played an influential role at CSA as the organisation struggled to bat away legal cases. READ: CSA accepts interim board Those cases were not just against individuals who worked at the federation but also some of its provincial affiliates. According to the report, Gwaza did not provide a due diligence report regarding Global Sports Commerce, a company CSA signed a commercial and broadcast deal with for the Mzansi Super League.